                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>kittykatvegas wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">ok I really need this explained to me...what exactly makes masturbation BAD????</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
There are several reasons why I think that masturbation is bad. But most of all, it has to do we the purpose of sex. I think sex is a wonderful thing that allows two fully committed partners to be happy with each other both physically and emotionally. If abused, it depreciates its value. Masturbation is one of the way it is mis-used imho. Second, it goes against how we human functions: whenever, we do something good, we feel "satisfied". The feeling of satisfactions encourages us to do something good. Sex between husband and wife helps them to maintain good relationship with each other. After jog, we feel satisfied which helps our body fit. After we help others in need, we are satisfied. After we get study/job done, we are satisfied. But things like drugs, smoking, drinking and masturbations, gives us short pleasure/satisfactions ... but it accomplishes nothing .... since it is "easy" to get, we just keep doing it to get more satisfactions but it is a dead end. One may argue, Masturbation is part of life in itself. I do not agree but different people draw different conclusions. I am not saying that drugs, smoking, drinking and masturbations are such deadly sins that separate good people from bad people or used as a criteria to categorize people. Different people have different weaknesses and dependencies. But what I do think is that the one who understand his weaknesses and not give up on improving them is the one who really appreciates happiness.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=664034" target="_blank" class="postlink">Primer</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
